{
  "text": "Originally a measure of inequality, the Gini coefficient is commonly employed as a measure of diversification at the industry-level, for instance in the context of sectoral and export diversification (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . I employ the Gini coefficient at the productlevel to examine the product revenue distribution and hence the product diversification of a firm.",
